      <h2>Step 5: Track and Follow Up</h2>
      <p>TradeQuote Pro provides a dashboard showing all sent estimates, their status (Sent, Viewed, Accepted, Declined, Expired), and the date of last activity. Review this dashboard daily:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Estimates viewed but not accepted</strong> — call to ask if they have questions. The client is interested but hesitating</li>
        <li><strong>Estimates not viewed after 48 hours</strong> — the email may have gone to spam, or they found another contractor. Follow up with a call</li>
        <li><strong>Accepted estimates</strong> — move to scheduling. Link them to your calendar or dispatch system</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Following up on estimates that have been viewed but not answered typically recovers 15–25% of otherwise lost bids. The tracking feature makes it trivial to know exactly who to call.</p>

      <h2>Advanced Tips for Power Users</h2>
      <p>Once the basics are down, these features take TradeQuote Pro to the next level:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Estimate bundles:</strong> Create packages (e.g., "Basic Roof Package," "Premium Roof Package") that upsell clients without needing multiple estimates</li>
        <li><strong>Cost history:</strong> The tool tracks material costs over time, so you can see when prices are trending up and adjust your quotes accordingly</li>
        <li><strong>Email templates:</strong> Customize the delivery email copy so every estimate sends with your personal intro note</li>
        <li><strong>Change order support:</strong> If scope changes mid-project, generate a change order that references the original estimate</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Why TradeQuote Pro Beats Spreadsheets</h2>
      <p>Spreadsheets and handwritten estimates create three problems that cost contractors real money. First, manual entry leads to calculation errors — a missed decimal or forgotten line item that turns a profitable job into a loss. Second, each estimate takes 30–45 minutes, so contractors rush through them and only send 3–5 per week. Third, there is no tracking — once the estimate leaves your hands, you have no idea whether the client read it, liked it, or deleted it.</p>
      <p>TradeQuote Pro solves all three. The math is automated and error-proof. Templates cut creation time to 5 minutes, so you can afford to quote more leads. And the tracking dashboard tells you exactly which estimates to follow up on, turning your quoting process into a repeatable sales machine.</p>

